WEBVTT

00:01.653 --> 00:08.660
♪

00:16.712 --> 00:22.152
all: I pledge
allegiance to the flag

00:22.196 --> 00:26.113
of the United States
of America,

00:26.156 --> 00:32.119
and to the Republic
for which it stands,

00:32.162 --> 00:36.688
one nation,
under God, indivisible.

00:36.732 --> 00:39.126
- With liberty
and justice for all.

00:40.779 --> 00:42.303
- Remember that pledge,

00:42.346 --> 00:45.567
because tonight
you will be tested.

00:45.610 --> 00:49.092
You'll be tried
in every imaginable way.

00:49.136 --> 00:52.182
But you will triumph

00:52.226 --> 00:55.490
if you show your allegiance
and Purge.

00:57.144 --> 00:58.841
It's going to be hell.

00:58.884 --> 01:01.409
But it's also a gift.

01:01.452 --> 01:04.151
Twelve hours of freedom.

01:04.194 --> 01:06.762
That's just over 43,000
seconds

01:06.805 --> 01:10.113
to change your life forever.

01:10.157 --> 01:13.595
But look,
I wouldn't lie to you.

01:13.638 --> 01:16.641
What I'm talking about--
it's hard.

01:16.685 --> 01:18.643
Not everyone's up for it.

01:18.687 --> 01:22.125
Participation is dangerous.
It's risky.

01:22.169 --> 01:27.783
But that risk gives way
to unyielding reward.

01:27.826 --> 01:31.830
So prepare, plan,
pray if you have to.

01:31.874 --> 01:34.181
Do whatever you need to do.

01:34.224 --> 01:37.662
Just make sure you're ready
for a world of possibility.

01:40.187 --> 01:43.755
Life is fleeting.
Blink and it's gone.

01:45.453 --> 01:47.629
But when you embrace
the Purge--

01:47.672 --> 01:51.546
when you commit to the healing
power of its violence--

01:51.589 --> 01:55.854
when you rise up, ready to
submit to its will...

01:55.898 --> 01:58.292
anything can happen.

01:58.335 --> 02:03.862
♪

02:17.224 --> 02:19.835
- Okay, enough bullshit.

02:19.878 --> 02:23.404
I'm tying up the girls,
then we move on.

02:30.541 --> 02:32.195
Paige.

02:32.239 --> 02:34.197
Come here.
Turn around.

02:34.241 --> 02:36.504
Put your hands
behind your back.

02:36.547 --> 02:39.376
It's working, just like
they said it would.

02:39.420 --> 02:41.726
I can feel it,
the power of the Purge.

02:41.770 --> 02:45.469
Penelope.
Come on.

02:45.513 --> 02:48.298
Please.
Come on!

02:53.695 --> 02:56.741
It's almost dawn.
We don't have much time.

02:56.785 --> 03:00.223
No more interruptions.
You too.

03:00.267 --> 03:02.399
Hey.

03:02.443 --> 03:04.488
On stage.
Now.

03:04.532 --> 03:08.231
Get up.

03:11.408 --> 03:14.281
When I walk out of here,

03:14.324 --> 03:16.674
I'm going to be free
of everything.

03:19.590 --> 03:22.289
- Charlie, Eileen, Jane.

03:22.332 --> 03:24.900
How is it fair
that you're free and we die?

03:24.943 --> 03:27.685
- That's the Purge, Jenna.
Sit down.

03:27.729 --> 03:29.557
It offers an equal
opportunity for everyone,

03:29.600 --> 03:32.255
a perfectly level
playing field.

03:32.299 --> 03:34.388
Any of you could
have come after me.

03:34.431 --> 03:35.563
But you didn't, did you?

03:35.606 --> 03:37.434
I took the initiative.

03:37.478 --> 03:41.351
I could have died ten times
over rounding each of you up.

03:41.395 --> 03:43.832
But I was willing to take the
risk 'cause I wanted it more.

03:43.875 --> 03:45.312
- Listen, my wife is--

03:45.355 --> 03:46.487
- Pregnant.

03:46.530 --> 03:47.923
I know.
Stop reminding me.

03:47.966 --> 03:49.272
- Please, just let her go.

03:55.452 --> 03:59.761
♪

03:59.804 --> 04:02.764
- Miguel, listen up.

04:02.807 --> 04:06.420
Lotta people depend on that
carnival to make their nut.

04:06.463 --> 04:10.424
This is the price
of being a hero, son.

04:10.467 --> 04:11.729
♪

04:11.773 --> 04:13.514
Fan out.
Find him.

04:13.557 --> 04:15.820
Pete, too.

04:15.864 --> 04:18.606
- Yeah, he ain't untouchable.

04:18.649 --> 04:20.303
And find them fast.

04:20.347 --> 04:22.958
We can't do jack shit
once that siren sounds.

04:23.001 --> 04:24.742
- All right,
let's sweep the area.

04:24.786 --> 04:26.483
- Pete,
we don't have time for this.

04:26.527 --> 04:27.745
- If we don't take care
of this right now,

04:27.789 --> 04:29.704
it follows us to the school.

04:29.747 --> 04:32.750
Look, we don't know
what's waiting for us there.

04:32.794 --> 04:36.363
Say we take a few out
right here and then we move.

04:36.406 --> 04:37.755
The guards will be easy,

04:37.799 --> 04:39.061
but Rex and the collectors,

04:39.104 --> 04:40.976
they round up people
for a living.

04:41.019 --> 04:42.891
They're strapped
and they're pissed.

04:42.934 --> 04:44.458
- But they're spreading out.

04:44.501 --> 04:46.460
- Yeah, trying
to cover more ground,

04:46.503 --> 04:50.551
but isolating themselves
while they do it.

04:50.594 --> 04:52.335
They think we're running.

04:52.379 --> 04:54.555
We go on offense.

04:54.598 --> 04:57.645
We surprise them.

04:57.688 --> 05:00.952
- Let's go.

05:03.999 --> 05:11.006
♪

05:19.406 --> 05:20.450
♪

05:23.714 --> 05:30.721
♪

06:26.995 --> 06:29.084
- Shit.

06:29.127 --> 06:31.739
You all right?
- Yeah. We should move on.

06:31.782 --> 06:33.131
School's this way.

06:33.175 --> 06:35.438
- Let's go.

06:35.482 --> 06:37.788
♪

06:43.141 --> 06:46.014
- Thank you
for going home tonight.

06:46.057 --> 06:48.756
Made my job a lot easier.

06:48.799 --> 06:50.584
I don't know if I could
have gotten into

06:50.627 --> 06:53.456
the Stanton compound
by myself.

06:53.500 --> 06:54.762
- How did you know
we were there?

06:54.805 --> 06:57.504
- I have been
following you for weeks.

06:58.896 --> 07:00.115
- Look, Mr. Owens
would you please--

07:00.158 --> 07:02.552
- Joe.
You remember when we met?

07:02.596 --> 07:03.945
That's what I told you
to call me.

07:03.988 --> 07:05.947
Come on, Rick, you remember.

07:05.990 --> 07:07.514
Mr. Betancourt.

07:07.557 --> 07:09.690
- Oh, please.
Call me Rick.

07:09.733 --> 07:11.082
- Joe.

07:11.126 --> 07:13.476
There you go.

07:13.520 --> 07:15.130
Can't believe
you picked this place.

07:15.173 --> 07:17.524
- Yeah.
I drove by it the other day

07:17.567 --> 07:19.874
and I realized I haven't
been here since high school.

07:19.917 --> 07:23.051
- Mm.

07:23.094 --> 07:24.792
I had a cousin
that worked at Saticoy.

07:24.835 --> 07:26.489
This was his spot,

07:26.533 --> 07:27.925
probably because
they never carded.

07:31.625 --> 07:32.843
- Schroeder.
- Yeah.

07:32.887 --> 07:34.932
- Great guy.
Hell of a line engineer.

07:34.976 --> 07:36.238
What's he up to?

07:36.281 --> 07:37.761
- Oh, when they closed
the factory,

07:37.805 --> 07:40.198
he moved in
with the in-laws and...

07:40.242 --> 07:43.506
We haven't kept in touch
since then unfortunately.

07:43.550 --> 07:47.989
- Yeah, it's tough
to bounce back after that.

07:48.032 --> 07:51.601
Some of us,
you know, we manage.

07:51.645 --> 07:54.125
Which I guess is why
we're sitting here, right?

07:54.169 --> 07:56.171
You saw my rate sheet.
What do you think?

07:56.214 --> 07:58.521
- Oh, this is a--
this is a big job.

07:58.565 --> 08:01.916
Plan is to start leasing
in the fall.

08:01.959 --> 08:06.834
- So you're going to need
Purge security on the building

08:06.877 --> 08:08.226
and the individual units?

08:08.270 --> 08:09.880
- That's correct.

08:09.924 --> 08:11.882
- Who's providing
the shell system?

08:11.926 --> 08:14.798
- Sandin.
- Oh, the best.

08:14.842 --> 08:16.539
- You've installed
for them before?

08:16.583 --> 08:18.149
- Absolutely.

08:18.193 --> 08:20.804
A bunch of homes
and a couple offices downtown.

08:20.848 --> 08:23.024
I can get you references
if you want them.

08:23.067 --> 08:25.592
- You've never done a building
of this size though, right?

08:25.635 --> 08:27.202
- It won't be a problem.

08:27.245 --> 08:31.554
I have been ready and waiting
for something like this.

08:31.598 --> 08:35.558
I mean, a contract like yours,
it's a level up,

08:35.602 --> 08:38.866
and I'd be excited
to tackle it.

08:38.909 --> 08:43.131
- Honestly,
it's a big step up for us too.

08:43.174 --> 08:44.828
I gotta tell you, Joe,

08:44.872 --> 08:46.264
I feel like I'm
constantly righting the ship.

08:46.308 --> 08:49.572
You know, putting out one fire
after the other.

08:49.616 --> 08:53.141
But...one big break
and it will all pay off, right?

08:53.184 --> 08:57.580
- I'm counting on it.

08:57.624 --> 08:59.582
I can start tomorrow?

08:59.626 --> 09:01.279
- I bet.

09:01.323 --> 09:05.066
No, why don't you send me your
quotes when you have them?

09:05.109 --> 09:07.895
We'll go over the numbers
and agree on a contract.

09:07.938 --> 09:09.592
Just remember,
we're a small outfit,

09:09.636 --> 09:10.724
so there's not much
wiggle room.

09:10.767 --> 09:13.596
- Got it.
Great.

09:13.640 --> 09:15.076
Do you wanna get a beer

09:15.119 --> 09:18.906
and celebrate our potential
partnership properly?

09:18.949 --> 09:21.648
- Sure, I could go for a beer.

09:21.691 --> 09:23.127
I'll get the first round.

09:23.171 --> 09:25.173
- And I'll tell you a great
story about your cousin.

09:25.216 --> 09:28.045
- Okay.

09:31.092 --> 09:32.093
♪

09:32.136 --> 09:34.312
- Shit.

09:34.356 --> 09:41.363
♪

09:55.812 --> 09:58.075
- I don't have to explain
what a contract is, do I?

09:58.119 --> 10:01.122
- I don't know,
do you know what a contract is?

10:01.165 --> 10:02.253
Because you agreed to it.

10:02.297 --> 10:03.907
- You took advantage.

10:03.951 --> 10:06.301
You used my inexperience
and my enthusiasm

10:06.344 --> 10:10.305
to make sure there was plenty
of room in here to screw me.

10:10.348 --> 10:12.089
I don't see your signature
here, Jenna.

10:12.133 --> 10:13.961
- Rick handles the contracts.

10:14.004 --> 10:16.659
- Is that so you don't dirty
your delicate little hands?

10:16.703 --> 10:18.182
- Because I trust him.

10:18.226 --> 10:19.662
- So did I.

10:19.706 --> 10:21.185
And then your husband
ruined me.

10:21.229 --> 10:24.319
He said my work was
subpar--negligent--

10:24.362 --> 10:25.407
so he wouldn't have to pay me.

10:25.450 --> 10:27.061
I lost all my other contracts

10:27.104 --> 10:29.237
just so your company
could save a few bucks.

10:29.280 --> 10:32.196
- Joe, we paid you
everything we owed

10:32.240 --> 10:34.329
and then you tried
to extort me.

10:34.372 --> 10:36.897
- I came to your office.
You saw.

10:36.940 --> 10:38.333
Do you remember, Jenna?

10:38.376 --> 10:40.814
We agreed on a number.

10:40.857 --> 10:42.946
I bought equipment,
custom software,

10:42.990 --> 10:44.992
I hired subcontractors
based on that.

10:45.035 --> 10:47.690
- Right, and I realize that

10:47.734 --> 10:49.257
but, look, none of the security
nodes passed the inspection.

10:49.300 --> 10:50.345
What do you want me to do?

10:50.388 --> 10:51.738
- I checked the system myself.

10:51.781 --> 10:53.217
Let me come in and fix it.

10:53.261 --> 10:55.045
I'm sure I can figure out
what went wrong.

10:55.089 --> 10:56.830
- Joe, I'm underwater here.

10:56.873 --> 10:59.180
I can't take any more delays.

10:59.223 --> 11:00.834
- Give me two days.

11:00.877 --> 11:02.792
- We already hired
somebody else.

11:02.836 --> 11:07.144
- So I have to just take your
word that the system's faulty?

11:07.188 --> 11:09.146
Let me see the admin log.

11:09.190 --> 11:10.365
- We're done here.

11:10.408 --> 11:12.106
- You're screwing me
and you know it.

11:12.149 --> 11:13.716
I did good work
and now you're pulling this?

11:13.760 --> 11:15.065
- We agreed on terms.

11:15.109 --> 11:17.241
- Yeah, but you put stuff
in the fine print

11:17.285 --> 11:19.461
that I couldn't
even pronounce.

11:19.504 --> 11:21.419
You bought me a beer, you
pretended to be my partner,

11:21.463 --> 11:23.030
all so you could bend me over?

11:23.073 --> 11:24.335
- Joe, your work was--

11:24.379 --> 11:25.728
- My work was top notch.

11:25.772 --> 11:27.382
But that doesn't matter,

11:27.425 --> 11:30.080
because I'm just cannon fodder
on your way to the top, right?

11:30.124 --> 11:31.734
Another fire to put out.

11:31.778 --> 11:35.042
- No, I wanted this to work.
I did.

11:35.085 --> 11:37.435
- This is going
to put me under.

11:37.479 --> 11:39.133
Do you even care?

11:39.176 --> 11:40.134
- I do and--

11:40.177 --> 11:41.744
- Then pay me, you prick!

11:43.050 --> 11:47.358
We don't want to have to
call the police.

11:47.402 --> 11:50.753
Please leave.

11:50.797 --> 11:53.190
- I know why you don't hang out
with your cousin Tony anymore.

11:53.234 --> 11:56.150
Because you're better than us
now, right?

11:56.193 --> 11:57.891
White collar.
Big shot.

11:57.934 --> 11:59.893
- Get out.

11:59.936 --> 12:03.853
- Go to hell,
you smug son of a bitch.

12:11.339 --> 12:14.081
So what, Jenna?

12:14.124 --> 12:15.778
Are you really that blind
to who you married

12:15.822 --> 12:17.258
or is it just willful
ignorance?

12:17.301 --> 12:19.521
- Jenna, I'm going to say
this one more time.

12:19.564 --> 12:24.874
We paid him
exactly what we owed.

12:24.918 --> 12:26.441
- She doesn't believe you.

12:26.484 --> 12:28.878
She sees you
for who you really are.

12:28.922 --> 12:33.230
- No, it's not my fault.
He did shoddy work.

12:33.274 --> 12:34.928
Jenna,
he wants to Purge Penelope

12:34.971 --> 12:37.017
because she didn't say
"thank you."

12:37.060 --> 12:40.455
Do you really trust
what he's saying?

12:40.498 --> 12:43.850
- You put us here.

12:53.424 --> 13:00.431
♪

13:18.319 --> 13:21.365
- It's just like the house.

13:21.409 --> 13:23.193
Damn it.

13:23.237 --> 13:24.499
- It's rigged
all the way around.

13:24.542 --> 13:26.327
- Probably.

13:26.370 --> 13:29.896
But I need to--

13:41.995 --> 13:45.215
- Let's go, Pete.
Move, move.

13:56.357 --> 13:59.882
♪

13:59.926 --> 14:04.887
- What does a signature
mean to you, Rick?

14:04.931 --> 14:08.369
To me, it represents a promise
made in good faith.

14:08.412 --> 14:11.198
A guarantee protected
by the rule of law.

14:11.241 --> 14:13.243
Now, tonight, the rule of law
is suspended.

14:13.287 --> 14:17.030
But during the rest of the year
we are bound by it.

14:17.073 --> 14:22.426
It is the only way our society
can function as intended.

14:25.038 --> 14:27.214
Don't you understand that?

14:27.257 --> 14:29.172
You're not above the law.

14:29.216 --> 14:34.177
You sign a contract,
you honor it.

14:34.221 --> 14:36.963
- Joe, I fulfilled every
element of that contract.

14:37.006 --> 14:38.921
You knew what you were signing.

14:38.965 --> 14:41.968
This isn't my fault.
The end didn't check out.

14:42.011 --> 14:44.971
♪

14:45.014 --> 14:48.061
- I think we lost them for now.

14:53.631 --> 14:57.244
- Fuck.
- This way.

15:11.084 --> 15:13.956
♪

15:14.000 --> 15:16.437
- Shit.
It's rigged on both sides.

15:16.480 --> 15:18.178
What's the play?

15:18.221 --> 15:20.571
- Can you take that one down
without it going off?

15:20.615 --> 15:22.095
Long enough for it to blow
somewhere else?

15:22.138 --> 15:24.271
- I think so.
Why?

15:24.314 --> 15:25.663
- Grab that one.

15:25.707 --> 15:28.101
I'll go back for
the one on the wall.

15:28.144 --> 15:29.580
- I'll cover you.

15:29.624 --> 15:32.453
- I got a stupid idea.

15:32.496 --> 15:34.150
- All right.

15:34.194 --> 15:39.634
♪

15:39.677 --> 15:43.203
- I was clearly within my
right to exercise discretion.

15:43.246 --> 15:44.639
The standard--
- There you go again,

15:44.682 --> 15:46.336
throwing $10 words at me

15:46.380 --> 15:47.468
because you think I can't
follow along.

15:49.035 --> 15:50.471
- I think I can
get us out of here.

15:50.514 --> 15:51.515
- Stop wasting our time.

15:52.690 --> 15:53.996
- Oh, yeah.

15:54.040 --> 15:55.563
- What I want is a confession.

15:55.606 --> 15:57.521
Come on, Rick,
tell the truth.

15:57.565 --> 16:01.482
- I am.
I paid you.

16:01.525 --> 16:04.746
- Doesn't even matter now.

16:04.789 --> 16:08.489
He's going to kill us.

16:08.532 --> 16:11.622
Maybe
this was the inevitable end.

16:11.666 --> 16:13.363
How can you say that?

16:13.407 --> 16:15.278
- We told ourselves we could
take the devil's money

16:15.322 --> 16:17.628
and do great things with it.
- Jenna...

16:17.672 --> 16:21.023
- I think the moment we decided
to take money from the devil,

16:21.067 --> 16:24.157
whatever the reason,

16:24.200 --> 16:25.593
we opened the door to this.

16:25.636 --> 16:28.335
- No. No, no.
We don't deserve this.

16:28.378 --> 16:29.553
- Confess.

16:29.597 --> 16:33.775
- I'm talking to my wife.

16:33.818 --> 16:36.038
- Look, I promise,
I would never--

16:36.082 --> 16:38.040
- Please, Rick.

16:38.084 --> 16:42.088
I don't want the last thing we
say to each other to be a lie.

16:42.131 --> 16:43.393
- I love you.

16:43.437 --> 16:46.048
- Confess.

16:46.092 --> 16:48.224
Confess!
Say it!

16:48.268 --> 16:52.054
- Okay! Okay...

16:52.098 --> 16:54.796
I did it.

16:54.839 --> 16:59.148
We took a bath
on the project downtown.

16:59.192 --> 17:02.760
And I had to cut costs.

17:02.804 --> 17:04.501
I found a loophole
in his contract,

17:04.545 --> 17:06.764
so I took advantage,

17:06.808 --> 17:08.679
but, I mean,
it's just part of business.

17:08.723 --> 17:10.377
- The loophole.

17:10.420 --> 17:14.772
- Jesus Christ.
You're not mad at me, Joe.

17:14.816 --> 17:16.165
You're mad at
the way things are.

17:16.209 --> 17:17.384
Just look around.

17:17.427 --> 17:19.168
This is the way
the world works.

17:19.212 --> 17:23.520
Everyone screws everyone
all the way down the line.

17:23.564 --> 17:26.393
You think I wasn't getting
squeezed by city managers?

17:26.436 --> 17:29.744
And the zoning board
and the Goddamn bank?

17:32.181 --> 17:36.577
I saw it do this to my parents
and it broke them.

17:36.620 --> 17:39.275
I wasn't going to let it happen
to us.

17:39.319 --> 17:40.711
- Are you ready
for your judgment?

17:40.755 --> 17:42.626
- Listen to me.

17:42.670 --> 17:45.760
I love you.

17:45.803 --> 17:47.849
I love you so much.

17:47.892 --> 17:50.504
And I'm sorry.

17:50.547 --> 17:53.768
- I love you, too.

17:53.811 --> 17:56.292
- She had nothing
to do with this, okay?

17:56.336 --> 17:58.686
She didn't--
she didn't even know.

17:58.729 --> 18:01.123
I know you're gonna kill me,
but--

18:01.167 --> 18:02.733
please can you just let her go?

18:02.777 --> 18:04.300
Let our daughter live.

18:04.344 --> 18:06.607
- Guilty by association.
- No! No, Jesus, no.

18:06.650 --> 18:07.869
I'll do anything.

18:07.912 --> 18:09.131
Please.

18:09.175 --> 18:11.612
- I know you will.

18:16.530 --> 18:18.445
I believe in fairness.

18:18.488 --> 18:20.490
And in compromise.

18:31.501 --> 18:34.330
I'm gonna give you a choice,
Jenna.

18:39.422 --> 18:42.164
Purge your husband.

18:42.208 --> 18:43.818
Teach him the consequences
of his actions

18:43.861 --> 18:47.648
and live to tell your daughter
what her father did.

18:47.691 --> 18:49.563
There's one bullet in this gun.

18:49.606 --> 18:51.347
If you use it on Rick,

18:51.391 --> 18:53.610
I'm gonna let you
and the baby live.

18:56.657 --> 18:57.832
♪

19:07.320 --> 19:09.844
♪

19:09.887 --> 19:12.586
The hell did they go?

19:12.629 --> 19:13.587
♪

19:15.937 --> 19:22.509
♪

19:22.552 --> 19:25.251
- Remind me again what the hell
we're doing out here.

19:27.253 --> 19:29.429
- Hurry.

19:33.824 --> 19:35.696
- Purge.

19:35.739 --> 19:37.828
- I can't.
Please.

19:37.872 --> 19:39.830
- Look, I'm not gonna waste
a lot of time with this.

19:39.874 --> 19:43.747
Either you pull the trigger
or I pull it twice.

19:48.578 --> 19:50.537
- Purge.

19:56.760 --> 19:59.676
- Do it.

19:59.720 --> 20:02.549
It's okay, Jenna.
It's okay.

20:14.996 --> 20:17.259
- Come on, come on, come on,
come on, come on.

20:17.303 --> 20:20.610
- Everything we've been through
tonight...

20:20.654 --> 20:25.572
Everything with Lila...

20:25.615 --> 20:27.400
You don't have to give
your life for me.

20:27.443 --> 20:30.403
- This is my fault, Jen.

20:30.446 --> 20:32.274
This is the only way out.

20:32.318 --> 20:36.278
- I'm so sorry, Rick.

20:36.322 --> 20:40.587
I got so wrapped up in
my own dreams, my feelings.

20:40.630 --> 20:41.936
I took what we had for granted.

20:41.979 --> 20:44.373
- No.
I love you.

20:44.417 --> 20:46.593
Do it.
- No.

20:46.636 --> 20:49.291
- For our baby, Jenna.
Do it.

20:57.691 --> 20:59.954
Good-bye.

20:59.997 --> 21:03.653
- Now!

21:09.355 --> 21:13.663
- Nice confession, Jenna.

21:13.707 --> 21:17.711
Did you really think I was
gonna give you a loaded weapon?

21:24.065 --> 21:26.023
Sit down.

21:26.067 --> 21:27.634
You and the baby are safe,

21:27.677 --> 21:29.853
because a deal is a deal,
right, Rick?

21:29.897 --> 21:34.815
- No, let me go!

21:34.858 --> 21:37.731
- It's my right to Purge.

21:37.774 --> 21:40.473
- Please, please don't kill me.
Please don't kill me.

21:40.516 --> 21:41.822
I don't want to d--

21:41.865 --> 21:48.872
♪

21:51.875 --> 21:55.052
- This son of a bitch.

21:57.925 --> 22:00.493
- Looks like you lost your hat.

22:02.408 --> 22:04.845
- There's a bounty on his head
for wrecking the carnival.

22:04.888 --> 22:07.500
- We collect,
I'm back in the black.

22:07.543 --> 22:09.023
- Maybe we can make a deal.

22:09.066 --> 22:11.634
- I don't want to make a deal
with you, Pete.

22:11.678 --> 22:13.375
You started all this shit.

22:15.464 --> 22:17.031
What's the bounty?

22:17.074 --> 22:19.120
I'll double it.

22:20.426 --> 22:23.385
- Just give me the number.

22:23.429 --> 22:25.909
- Call Miguel out here first.

22:29.130 --> 22:30.871
- Get away from her.

22:30.914 --> 22:32.568
- I have the right,
same as you.

22:32.612 --> 22:35.789
I need to cleanse.

22:35.832 --> 22:37.007
- Don't you dare.

22:37.051 --> 22:41.011
She is mine to purge.

22:41.055 --> 22:43.884
Put it down, now.

22:43.927 --> 22:47.496
I'll pay it.

22:47.540 --> 22:51.805
Hell, I'll bankrupt my bar if I
have to to save his life.

22:51.848 --> 22:54.155
Or would you rather
just shoot him, dead?

22:54.198 --> 22:59.552
'Cause you're just a petty,
bloodthirsty little shit.

22:59.595 --> 23:00.727
♪

23:00.770 --> 23:03.599
- If I'm being honest,

23:03.643 --> 23:06.428
it's a little of both.

23:08.517 --> 23:12.913
- Oh, sh--

23:17.831 --> 23:21.748
- Come on!
Go, go, go, go, go, go.

23:23.967 --> 23:27.971
Come on!
- Go, go, go, go, run!

23:28.015 --> 23:34.195
♪

23:34.238 --> 23:37.677
- These sons of bitches
got bamboozled.

23:37.720 --> 23:40.941
- Let's go, they're down.

24:24.767 --> 24:26.552
Come on, do it.
You gotta do it.

24:26.595 --> 24:29.032
You gotta do it.
You gotta do it.

24:40.043 --> 24:42.829
I am not gonna let
that bitch ruin me.

24:42.872 --> 24:47.747
♪

24:47.790 --> 24:50.793
I'm coming!

25:00.716 --> 25:07.723
♪

25:09.116 --> 25:11.205
- Clear.

25:11.248 --> 25:14.556
♪

25:14.600 --> 25:16.689
- Clear.

25:16.732 --> 25:18.691
♪

25:18.734 --> 25:20.954
Clear.

25:20.997 --> 25:24.305
♪

25:24.348 --> 25:27.917
- Ready.
Go.

25:27.961 --> 25:29.745
- Jenna, get back!
- Put it down!

25:29.789 --> 25:32.792
- Drop it! Now, drop it!
- Put the gun down, now!

25:32.835 --> 25:34.707
♪

25:34.750 --> 25:38.014
We're not here for you, okay?
Look.

25:40.713 --> 25:43.324
We're here for my sister.

25:43.367 --> 25:45.326
- Rick, it's okay.

25:45.369 --> 25:47.720
It's okay.

25:47.763 --> 25:49.156
- Easy.

25:49.199 --> 25:51.593
- Okay.

25:51.637 --> 25:53.029
- Her name's Penelope.
Has she--

25:53.073 --> 25:55.597
- She's alive--she's here.
She saved us.

25:57.120 --> 25:59.122
- I don't know, she ran ahead.
We got separated.

25:59.166 --> 26:01.734
- He's here, too.

26:01.777 --> 26:03.257
- You're gonna come with us.
We'll keep you safe.

26:04.650 --> 26:06.913
- Thank you, my family is...

26:06.956 --> 26:09.045
Get back, Jenna!

26:13.136 --> 26:16.705
- Pete, I'm hit.

26:16.749 --> 26:19.229
- It's okay.
- He got me in the leg.

26:20.666 --> 26:21.797
- No, it's nothing, man.
I'm fine.

26:21.841 --> 26:22.972
I'm fine.
- Let me check on it.

26:23.016 --> 26:24.234
- No, no.
I've got those two.

26:24.278 --> 26:25.322
You gotta get out here.

26:25.366 --> 26:26.323
Now, find Penelope.

26:26.367 --> 26:27.368
- Pete.
- Go.

26:27.411 --> 26:30.153
Miguel, now.
Go.

26:33.069 --> 26:36.638
You gotta push.
Put pressure on it.

26:36.682 --> 26:39.946
Press hard.

26:39.989 --> 26:42.078
- You're okay, man.
You're okay.

26:42.122 --> 26:44.646
- Okay, okay.

26:51.131 --> 26:52.175
- Come on, this way.
- No, no, this way!

26:52.219 --> 26:54.656
We have to stay together.

26:58.747 --> 27:01.663
Paige!
Oh, my God.

27:04.710 --> 27:07.016
♪

27:10.063 --> 27:13.980
♪

27:14.023 --> 27:16.939
- Penelope!

27:16.983 --> 27:23.990
♪

28:02.898 --> 28:05.466
- Let's just get on a
cruise and go to Tahiti.

28:10.079 --> 28:11.341
- Yeah.

28:11.385 --> 28:14.736
- Okay.

28:14.780 --> 28:17.870
- Hey, you should
take her away.

28:17.913 --> 28:20.220
Let her grow
up anywhere but here.

28:20.263 --> 28:24.746
- No, no, we're getting
you to a hospital.

28:24.790 --> 28:26.182
Rick?

28:26.226 --> 28:29.446
- Just give her--
give her a kiss for me.

28:31.100 --> 28:33.886
- Rick...

28:33.929 --> 28:36.976
No...Rick.

28:37.019 --> 28:40.153
♪

28:43.199 --> 28:45.245
Rick.
Rick.

28:59.999 --> 29:04.873
- We need to put some distance
between us and Joe.

29:04.917 --> 29:07.006
We gotta go.
- No.

29:07.049 --> 29:08.790
Rick, I'm sorry.

29:08.834 --> 29:11.271
- We'll come back for him
when it's safe.

29:25.024 --> 29:26.939
- Let go of me!

29:26.982 --> 29:28.984
- You little bitch.

29:29.028 --> 29:31.508
You almost ruined everything.

29:33.119 --> 29:34.816
- But right now we can
have the trial.

29:34.860 --> 29:37.819
Just the two of us.

29:43.564 --> 29:46.045
- Thank you
for holding the door.

29:47.524 --> 29:49.265
It's a little late
for that now.

29:49.309 --> 29:51.398
- We give people one strike
in this country now?

29:51.441 --> 29:54.314
- Don't talk to me about
what we do in this country.

29:54.357 --> 29:55.837
Where the hell were you born?

29:55.881 --> 29:58.231
- Staten Island.

29:58.274 --> 29:59.232
- What difference
does that make?

29:59.275 --> 30:00.537
This is our home.

30:00.581 --> 30:01.887
- This country
used to be a place

30:01.930 --> 30:03.410
where everybody
could thrive.

30:03.453 --> 30:04.846
- Not everybody.

30:04.890 --> 30:06.326
- All that hope
and change bullshit

30:06.369 --> 30:09.024
didn't get us anywhere.

30:09.068 --> 30:12.027
America was circling
the drain until the Purge.

30:12.071 --> 30:13.507
Suddenly each of us
had the power

30:13.550 --> 30:15.030
to make things better
and we did.

30:15.074 --> 30:16.945
- At every point.

30:16.989 --> 30:19.339
- No.
I woke up today convinced

30:19.382 --> 30:21.471
that my life only had value
if I was a victim.

30:21.515 --> 30:23.169
I was wrong.
- Oh, come on.

30:23.212 --> 30:27.216
You know you don't have it
in you to be anything else.

30:27.260 --> 30:30.437
When the rains come and
flood this rock, will you...

30:30.480 --> 30:32.526
both: Sink or swim?
Will you drown?

30:32.569 --> 30:35.529
- Or fight your way to shore.

30:35.572 --> 30:37.879
Yeah, Bobby Sheridan.

30:37.923 --> 30:39.489
Tavis played us his lectures.

30:39.533 --> 30:41.404
Said we needed to understand
why Purgers are broken,

30:41.448 --> 30:43.189
so we can
learn how to help them.

30:43.232 --> 30:45.191
- Then you know exactly
why I'm doing this.

30:45.234 --> 30:49.021
- I do. I just don't know why
you believe it will help.

30:49.064 --> 30:51.545
- Because for me,

30:51.588 --> 30:54.548
it can't get any worse.

30:54.591 --> 30:57.203
God bless America,
where I have the freedom

30:57.246 --> 31:00.032
to decide
for myself what's right

31:00.075 --> 31:04.036
and the freedom to change
my circumstances.

31:04.079 --> 31:07.300
- This might be your America,
but it's not mine.

31:10.129 --> 31:12.305
- Right now
it's the only one that matters.

31:12.348 --> 31:13.567
- No.
The country you're destroying--

31:13.610 --> 31:15.177
I want to help rebuild.

31:15.221 --> 31:16.352
And I'm not the only one.

31:16.396 --> 31:19.007
- Huh.

31:19.051 --> 31:20.966
- I see people that fight
every day

31:21.009 --> 31:22.619
to protect this country,

31:22.663 --> 31:25.274
even after
it took everything from them.

31:25.318 --> 31:27.494
♪

31:27.537 --> 31:29.409
And I see people--
complete strangers--

31:29.452 --> 31:32.238
picking each other up,
not tearing each other down.

31:32.281 --> 31:34.457
♪

31:34.501 --> 31:38.113
And I see other people--
desperate, angry people--

31:38.157 --> 31:39.941
hurting each other every year

31:39.985 --> 31:42.161
because they've been
manipulated into doing it.

31:44.990 --> 31:47.253
So Purge all you want.

31:47.296 --> 31:49.124
But when you're done,
what will be left?

31:49.168 --> 31:51.257
A nation of murderers.

31:51.300 --> 31:54.695
If Purging really worked--if
everyone actually got better--

31:54.738 --> 31:58.133
wouldn't we stop needing it?

31:58.177 --> 32:01.180
♪

32:01.223 --> 32:06.315
- Like our great nation,
I will be reborn.

32:10.015 --> 32:12.321
- Pen!

32:19.676 --> 32:21.069
- It's okay.

32:21.113 --> 32:23.289
It's over now.

32:23.332 --> 32:25.378
It's all over.

32:37.172 --> 32:44.179
♪

32:58.498 --> 33:00.717
- God damn it.

33:05.070 --> 33:07.028
- Finally.

33:11.815 --> 33:15.297
- God damn it.

33:15.341 --> 33:17.734
It wasn't supposed
to end this way.

33:22.087 --> 33:25.177
I was so looking forward

33:25.220 --> 33:28.354
to this morning,
my clean slate.

33:28.397 --> 33:30.312
- What the fuck
are you talking about?

33:30.356 --> 33:32.053
- I failed.

33:32.097 --> 33:34.403
All that work I did and
almost none of it went right.

33:36.753 --> 33:40.279
Just like life.

33:40.322 --> 33:42.063
God damn it.

33:45.240 --> 33:47.634
Now we get back to normal.

33:47.677 --> 33:51.203
Come on.
Without rules...

33:51.246 --> 33:53.161
We're animals.

33:53.205 --> 33:56.251
I'm a law-abiding citizen.

33:56.295 --> 33:58.123
The Purge is over.

33:58.166 --> 33:59.254
Take it.

33:59.298 --> 34:01.300
Take your sister and go home.

34:01.343 --> 34:02.475
♪

34:02.518 --> 34:03.824
- Let's go.

34:03.867 --> 34:05.565
- I'll catch up with you guys
next year.

34:06.609 --> 34:10.222
- Yeah.
Next Purge.

34:10.265 --> 34:12.702
I'll finish it
with both of you.

34:20.797 --> 34:25.106
Miguel, it's murder.

34:25.150 --> 34:31.808
♪

34:38.685 --> 34:41.383
- You'll do a lot of good work
on Purge night,

34:41.427 --> 34:45.605
but you won't be able
to get it all done.

34:45.648 --> 34:48.129
You'll taste failure.

34:48.173 --> 34:50.131
People will
always surprise you

34:50.175 --> 34:52.699
when they don't
want to die.

35:23.382 --> 35:25.601
- He's dead.

35:25.645 --> 35:27.473
- I figured.

35:27.516 --> 35:30.171
I heard the shots.

35:30.215 --> 35:31.738
Yeah.

35:31.781 --> 35:35.307
Just beforethe sirens.

35:35.350 --> 35:38.179
You know what I'm saying?

35:38.223 --> 35:41.443
- I do.

35:41.487 --> 35:45.186
♪

35:45.230 --> 35:46.535
- But don't worry.

35:46.579 --> 35:48.842
That's the beauty
of this holiday.

35:48.885 --> 35:52.237
Purge night ends,

35:52.280 --> 35:55.327
but the Purge goes on and on.

35:55.370 --> 35:57.459
What you didn't
accomplish tonight...

35:57.503 --> 35:59.592
there's always next year.

36:06.990 --> 36:08.688
- Go and call this guy.
- All right.

36:10.646 --> 36:12.735
- All right.
- It's bullshit.

36:13.910 --> 36:16.261
- Hey, Pete, look.

36:16.304 --> 36:17.871
- Look what the cat dragged in.

36:17.914 --> 36:19.220
- Hey, Pete.

36:21.396 --> 36:23.964
- Have a drink with me
before you head out?

36:24.007 --> 36:25.444
- I'll take a whiskey.

36:25.487 --> 36:26.445
- No, you will not
take a whiskey.

36:26.488 --> 36:28.229
You're not 21.

36:28.273 --> 36:31.537
- So I can kill people tonight
but I can't drink?

36:31.580 --> 36:34.496
- It's a good point.
whiskeys all around?

36:47.727 --> 36:51.252
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

36:51.296 --> 36:54.255
[indistinct announcement
in French]

36:54.299 --> 36:56.257
- Nice.

37:02.742 --> 37:05.614
Okay.
Okay.

37:30.944 --> 37:32.511
- After how last year ended,

37:32.554 --> 37:35.296
are you sure I can't
convince you to stay?

37:35.340 --> 37:37.472
- This is what our parents
would have wanted us to do.

37:37.516 --> 37:38.908
- They'd be proud...

37:38.952 --> 37:41.781
of both of you.

37:41.824 --> 37:44.610
- It's almost commencement.

37:44.653 --> 37:46.916
- Yup.
- Okay.

37:46.960 --> 37:48.962
But if you get jammed up...

37:49.005 --> 37:52.487
- No, I'll take care of him.
I'm the brains of this outfit.

37:56.012 --> 37:59.015
- Semper fi, brother.
- Oorah.

38:00.930 --> 38:02.628
- It's a military thing.

38:02.671 --> 38:04.978
Oorah's not a real word.

38:05.021 --> 38:06.632
- It means
stop asking questions

38:06.675 --> 38:08.808
and keep it moving, soldier.

38:08.851 --> 38:11.550
Come on.

38:11.593 --> 38:14.683
- Oorah.

38:19.035 --> 38:20.820
- In the wake of last year's
brutal attacks,

38:20.863 --> 38:23.823
NFAA loyalty squads
have worked double time,

38:23.866 --> 38:25.999
trying to curb
the threat of so-called

38:26.042 --> 38:28.741
"revolutionary Purge
night terrorism."

38:28.784 --> 38:29.959
There is a hush now
over the city

38:30.003 --> 38:32.005
as Purge commencement looms.

38:32.048 --> 38:35.356
Hopefully you and your loved
ones are safe in your homes,

38:35.400 --> 38:36.966
as we should start to hear

38:37.010 --> 38:39.012
the emergency services
announcement at any--

38:39.055 --> 38:42.494
- This is your emergency...
- And that's it, another Purge

38:42.537 --> 38:44.365
is now underway.

38:44.409 --> 38:45.932
My camera crew and I
are going to go inside

38:45.975 --> 38:47.368
where it's a
little bit safer.

38:50.415 --> 38:54.549
♪

38:54.593 --> 38:58.379
- Come on.

39:00.512 --> 39:03.384
- Thanks.

39:03.428 --> 39:05.908
Hopefully I won't need it,
but you know how it goes.

39:05.952 --> 39:11.044
♪

39:11.087 --> 39:12.611
Ready, Pen?

39:12.654 --> 39:13.742
- Yeah.

39:13.786 --> 39:16.136
Let's go save some lives.

39:16.179 --> 39:19.139
